<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 27 at 7:39PM MDT  by NWS Glasgow</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southwestern
Roosevelt, northeastern McCone, northwestern Dawson and northwestern
Richland Counties through 845 PM MDT...
At 739 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Wolf Point, moving northeast at 20 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Wolf Point, Poplar, Vida and Sprole.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
